==English==
===Pronunciation===
*SAMPA: /<tt>TIk</tt>/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'θɪk/

===Adjective===
'''thick''' ('''thicker''', '''thickest''')
# [[relatively]] [[great]] in [[extent]] from one [[surface]] to the [[opposite]]; not [[thin]]
#*Note: refers to the [[smallest]] [[solid]] [[dimension]] - compare [[wide]]
# [[measuring]] a [[specified]] [[number]] of [[unit]]s in this dimension
#* I want some 2 inch '''thick''' planks
# [[heavy]] in [[build]]; [[thickset]]
#* He had such a '''thick''' neck that he had to turn his body
# [[densely]] [[crowded]] or [[packed]]
#* we walked through '''thick''' undergrowth
# having a [[viscous]] [[consistency]]
#* My mum's gravy was '''thick''' but, at least, it moved about
# [[abounding]] in [[number]]
#* The room was '''thick''' with reporters
# [[inpenetrable]] to [[sight]]
#* We drove through '''thick''' fog
# [[difficult]] to [[understand]], or [[poorly]] [[articulated]]
#* We had difficulty with his '''thick''' accent
#(''informal'') [[stupid]]
#* He was as '''thick''' as two short planks
#(''informal'') [[friendly]] or [[intimate]]
#* They were as '''thick''' as thieves
===Adverb===
'''thick'''
# in a thick manner
#* Snow lay '''thick''' on the ground
# [[thickly]]
#* Bread should be sliced '''thick''' to make toast
===Noun===
'''thick'''
# the thickest, or most [[active]] or [[intense]] part of something
#* It was mayhem in the '''thick''' of battle

